Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, sprinkle
over the @lemon & herb seasoning{1%packet}, add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve, peel, and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into
small pieces.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

Cut the @medium tomato{1}(into 1cm chunks) into 1cm chunks.

Add the tomato chunks to a #medium bowl{} with half the @cider vinegar{30%ml},
a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} and the @sugar for the dressing{½%tsp}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside for now.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on
medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, lay the @British chicken thighs{4} flat in the frying pan.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry until browned on each side and cooked
through, ~{13-15%minutes}. Turn every ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken has finished cooking, transfer to a #plate and cover with
#foil to rest.

Return the (now empty) frying pan with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} (if needed) on
medium heat.

Add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and
cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Pour the remaining @cider vinegar{} into the pan and allow it to evaporate,
~{30%seconds}. Add the @water{100%ml} and @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Bring to
the boil, then lower the heat and simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir through the @butter{30%g} and parsley until the butter is melted. Simmer
until the sauce is thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Just before you are ready to serve, toss the @wild rocket{20%g} through the
dressing.

Share the chicken between your plates. Spoon over the buttery sauce.

Serve with your chips and salad alongside. Enjoy!